        "content": "**This dashboard covers what `api.ligate.io` (Infinity REST) can serve today.** The full operator view (mempool depth, RPC latency, process CPU/RSS, DA submission failure breakdown, etc.) requires a Prometheus scraper running against the chain VM's `127.0.0.1:9100/metrics` endpoint.\n\n**That work is tracked in:**\n- [ligate-chain#316](https://github.com/ligate-io/ligate-chain/issues/316) \u2014 Ops deploy punchlist (Prometheus + Alertmanager + Fluent Bit)\n- [ligate-chain#360](https://github.com/ligate-io/ligate-chain/issues/360) \u2014 Pre-mainnet security gap tracker\n- [ligate-chain#318](https://github.com/ligate-io/ligate-chain/issues/318) \u2014 Slack workspace + alertmanager webhook\n\nOnce a Grafana Cloud Agent is installed on the chain VM and scrapes to `grafanacloud-ligate-prom`, the operator-only panels (currently shipping with `ops/grafana/ligate-node.json` in the chain repo) can be re-imported alongside this one.",
